<title>UK: Triplex buys Thyssen unit.</title>
<headline>Triplex buys Thyssen unit.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>British engineering group Triplex Lloyd Plc said on Tuesday it had bought German castings company Feingusswerk Bochum from Thyssen Guss AG, a member of the Thyssen AG vorm August Thyssen-Huette metals group.</p>
<p>Triplex said it would pay an initial 17 million marks in cash for the company, which manufactures cast blades and vanes for turbine engines. An additional payment of up to 10 million marks was payable if certain turnover targets were met in the next five years, Triplex said.  </p>
<p>Triplex said it would set up a new subsdiary named TFB Feingusswerk Bochum GmbH to operate the business. TFB would be part of Triplex Lloyd's power generation division.</p>
